  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We generalize the differential representation of the operators of the Galilean algebras to include fractional derivatives. As a result a whole new class of scale invariant Galilean algebras are obtained. The first member of this class has dynamical index <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math> similar to the Schrödinger algebra. The second member of the class has dynamical index <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mn>2</mn></math> , which happens to be the dynamical index Kardar–Parisi–Zhang equation.</subfield>
